f reasonably anticipated charges for nonemergency health care services does not apply to an emergency department.(h) A hospital that fails to comply with the requirements of this section, is subject to sanctions by the Office of Health Facility Licensure and Certification, which includes the assessment of a civil monetary penalty not to exceed $1,000 for each violation.NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to require hospital to disclose price and fee information for certain hospital services.Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: